\section{Comparison with the theory}
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

A reference value for ${\cal R}$ has been computed
at NLO using the MCFM tool~\cite{Campbell:2003dd,Maltoni:2005wd,Campbell:2005zv} 
and the following parameters: 
\begin{itemize}
\item factorization and renormalization scales: $\mu_F=\mu_R$=91 GeV
\item PDF set: cteq6mE 
\end{itemize}
Table~\ref{tab:mcfm_scale_parameters} summarizes the results
for the individual cross sections and for their ratio obtained with the
above reference values and for a complete set of different renormalization and
factorization scales changed from $\times$1/2 to $\times$2 or
choosing as scale $M_Z^2+p^2_T(Z)$ or $<p_T^2(jet)>$.

The relative changes of the individual cross sections and of their
ratio as a function of $\mu_F$ and $\mu_F$ is shown in Figure~\ref{fig:zbzj_alphaRalphaF}.

